1) In Angular, (click)="openpopup()" is an event binding. Let me break it down for you:

1️⃣ Why ()?
The parentheses () bind events in Angular.
This means that when the event occurs (like a click), Angular will execute the assigned method.
2️⃣ Why (click)?
(click) specifically listens to the click event on an element.
Other events can also be used, like (mouseover), (keyup), (change), etc.


2) In your Angular component, this.show = true; is used to update a class property. Let's break it down:

1️⃣ Why this?
In TypeScript (and JavaScript classes), this refers to the current instance of the class.
When you define show as a property inside your Angular component, you access it using this.show.
